        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 8:45PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>The combination of accumulating dry fuels and low relative
humidity will continue to lead to increased fire danger Friday.
Relative humidity values will drop to around 30 percent Friday
afternoon and, with an abundance of dry fuels available, these
conditions could result in adverse fire behavior.
</description>
        <instruction>A burn ban remains in effect for for the area until further
notice. This also means all burning permits have been cancelled.
PLEASE, heed the burn ban in order to mitigate any additional
uncontained wildfires.</instruction>
